reviewText: I've seen the 3 Columbia films a number of times now, but Mill Creek has done a wonderful job with the best elements they could find.  And trust me, they look great!  John Wayne doesn't have a whole lot of screen time in these Columbia films (thanks Harry Cohn, you idiot), but the stories are fun.  Don't wait another second and grab this collection...you won't be sorry!
GREAT Wayne! Early films of the Dukes superb persona helped him become a better actor; he was born an icon!
I love John Wayne movies. Good addition to my collection.

This is a collection of a few of the early western serials. The part that I like is that John Wayne does all of his own stunt work and sometimes they expand on reality a bit. If you are a fan of John Wayne and want to see him in another great movie, you should watch some of the serials that he made early in his career. After watching a few of these its easy to see how he became the great Hollywood star he was!

IF YOU WANT TO SEE JOHN AFTER THE BIG TRAIL IN 1930, YOU GO TO COLUMBIA.
